                            <comment id="15031681" author="gagravarr" created="Mon, 30 Nov 2015 11:39:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The JSON license has been approved for use by Apache Projects by the ASF Legal Affairs committee, without affecting the license conditions of the overall software, see &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.apache.org/legal/resolved.html#json&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.apache.org/legal/resolved.html#json&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you feel that&apos;s incorrect, you&apos;d need to take that up with the Legal Affairs committee on legal-discuss@ - they&apos;re the ones qualified / charged with deciding on this sort of stuff, not us!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15031694" author="puntogil" created="Mon, 30 Nov 2015 12:00:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi&lt;br/&gt;
It did not surprise me much, ASL license then follow your intentions it is no longer free.&lt;br/&gt;
Wishing you could deduce that it slipped to a lower category of &quot;B&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
Regards&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15031879" author="chrismattmann" created="Mon, 30 Nov 2015 14:53:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=puntogil&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;puntogil&quot;&gt;puntogil&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=nick&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;nick&quot;&gt;nick&lt;/a&gt; - Nick answered and beat me to it. The ASF considers this license OK to include in ASF products: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.apache.org/legal/resolved.html#json&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.apache.org/legal/resolved.html#json&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus it shouldn&apos;t be a problem at all. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15031880" author="chrismattmann" created="Mon, 30 Nov 2015 14:54:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Per &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.apache.org/legal/resolved.html#json&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.apache.org/legal/resolved.html#json&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15670021" author="gagravarr" created="Wed, 16 Nov 2016 10:05:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The ASF legal team have recently changed their mind on the license (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/9627a9278d263378a2045d4bffccb6e83b9f01bb783c6dd6fa325faf@%3Clegal-discuss.apache.org%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/9627a9278d263378a2045d4bffccb6e83b9f01bb783c6dd6fa325faf@%3Clegal-discuss.apache.org%3E&lt;/a&gt;), so we&apos;ll now need to change this&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15678151" author="gagravarr" created="Fri, 18 Nov 2016 23:51:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ted Dunning has produced a hopefully drop-in replacement (based on a suitable library I believe, with method signatures tweaked). We could give this a try, and check everything passes - might be quicker and easier than swapping the whole json implementation...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;dependency&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;groupId&amp;gt;com.tdunning&amp;lt;/groupId&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;artifactId&amp;gt;json&amp;lt;/artifactId&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;version&amp;gt;1.0&amp;lt;/version&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/dependency&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could someone try that and see if all unit tests still pass?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15776304" author="thammegowda" created="Sun, 25 Dec 2016 10:41:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I attempted to fix this, but I hit a blocker:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;org.apache.tika.parser.journal.TEIParser uses org.json.XML.toJSONObject() method. This utility method doesn&apos;t exists in the replacement library. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Almost all the references I found on the internet for &quot;converting XML to JSON string&quot; points to the same code example I am trying to get rid off!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15798104" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Wed, 4 Jan 2017 12:19:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Y, I ran into the same problem...it shouldn&apos;t be too hard to write a SAX parser for the original XML and get rid of json entirely.  I&apos;m frankly lazy and haven&apos;t bothered getting the journal parser running locally.  If someone could share example xml output, it shouldn&apos;t take more than a few hours, I&apos;d think.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
