                            <comment id="16058231" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Wed, 21 Jun 2017 21:05:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=nick&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;nick&quot;&gt;nick&lt;/a&gt;, I dropped Ted Dunning&apos;s replacement in, refactored the TEIParser dramatically, and everything works.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I noticed that deeplearning4j still uses org.json, so I excluded that, on the theory, that tika-dl requires tika-parsers, which would bring in Ted Dunning&apos;s replacement.  As long as nothing in dl4j is calling &lt;tt&gt;toJSONObject()&lt;/tt&gt;, we &lt;em&gt;should&lt;/em&gt; be ok???&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyone know if that&apos;ll cause a problem?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, even though I installed grobid and got it running.  I get timeout errors on the test file, so I can&apos;t test grobid...  I did dump TEI.xml from one pdf, and the old and the new are equivalent.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, once I make the commit, it would be great if someone with a grobid that works on our test document could try it out.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
